===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{Han compound|囗|卪|t1=enclosure; city wall|t2=kneeling person|ls=ic}}. The bottom part of the radical is unrelated to [[巴]] and the top component is most likely unrelated to the original version of [[丁]].

===Etymology===
Possibly {{der|zh|sit}}. {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} proposes two possible etymologies:
* From {{cog|sit-pro|*Ɂip||shelter}}, whence also {{och-l|葺|thatch}}. Said root is apparently [[allofam]]ic with {{cog|tbq-pro|*jip|*s-y(i/u)p|t=to sleep}}, whence {{cog|my|အိပ်|t=to sleep}} (STEDT).
* Related to {{cog|sit-pro|*k-jim ~ k-jum||house}}, whence {{cog|my|အိမ်}}, {{cog|bo|ཁྱིམ}}.

